  "A key property of Gram-Schmidt is that for each k, span{u1,...,uk} = span{v1,...,vk}. So span{u1, u2} = span{v1, v2}.": "",
  "Apply Gram-Schmidt to v1 = (1, 1, 0) and v2 = (1, 0, 1). What is the orthogonal component u2 = v2 - proj_{u1}(v2)?": "",
